# JLens Architecture

JLens is a client-side JSON debugger: React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7, Tailwind 4, Zustand 5.

## Layer Separation

```
src/core/     Pure logic (parser, search, diff, share, repair) — zero React imports
src/stores/   Zustand stores — state + actions, no UI logic
src/hooks/    React hooks bridging stores ↔ components
src/components/ UI components — read from stores via hooks/selectors
src/workers/  Web Worker for heavy operations (>5MB payloads)
```

- Core modules must never import React, Zustand, or any UI library.
- Stores must never import components or hooks.
- New features go through: types → core logic → store integration → hook (if needed) → component.

## Key Data Structure

JSON is parsed into a flat `Map<string, JsonNode>` (not a nested tree). Paths are node IDs: `$`, `$.users`, `$.users[0].name`. Every node has `parentId` and `childIds` for traversal.

## Principles

- YAGNI — only build what's specified. No "nice to have" additions.
- Bundle budget: keep gzipped build under 120KB. Avoid heavy dependencies.
- All processing is client-side. No backend, no API calls (until v2.0).
- Test with Vitest: core logic gets unit tests, stores get integration tests.
